   Category: Income Support

   As a person with a disability, you might be eligible for monthly
   benefits and other financial assistance from the government. President
   Bush has committed to sign an order that directs the federal agency to
   swiftly implement the law giving Americans with disabilities the
   ability to choose their own support services and maintain their health
   benefits when they return to work. New Freedom Initiative

   Other Income Support
   Social Security Disability Insurance (SSDI)
   Social Security Work Incentives
   Supplemental Security Income (SSI)
   Temporary Assistance for Needy Families
   Veteran's Benefits

